===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₁lewdʰ-}}
Sense 1 (“especially of the will: free, independent”) is borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|libre|t=at liberty, free; clear, free, vacant; free, without obligation}}, from {{der|en|la|līber|t=free, unrestricted}},<ref>{{R:OED Online|entry=† libre|pos=adj|id=107929|date=1902}}</ref> ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₁lewdʰ-|t=people}}.

Senses 2 (“(''software'') with very few limitations on distribution or improvement”) and 3 ("not enslaved") are either borrowed from the French word or the {{bor|en|es|libre|t=free: not enslaved or imprisoned; without obligation; unconstrained by distrust or timidity; not containing, without}}, from the same Latin {{glossary|etymon}} as above.

